\section{Capturing the result of one shell session}

The runner only needs four facts from a completed session: when it
started, when it ended, the shell's exit status, and the captured
transcript.

<<classes>>=
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class ShellResult:
    """Captured result of one shell session."""

    started_at: str
    ended_at: str
    exit_status: int
    transcript: str
@

Let's verify that the result object keeps the captured transcript text.

<<test functions>>=
def test_shell_result_stores_transcript_text():
    result = ShellResult(
        started_at="2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00",
        ended_at="2026-01-01T00:00:01+00:00",
        exit_status=0,
        transcript="pwd\r\n",
    )

    assert "pwd" in result.transcript
